## Commit & Pull Request Guidelines

- Commit subjects use conventional-commit-ish prefixes: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`.
- Subject line ≤ 72 chars. Body wraps at ~80 cols.
- One logical change per commit. If you can split it, split it.

## Document Conventions

- **Progressive disclosure for growing docs.** When a doc exceeds ~30 discrete entries (e.g. a deferred-work backlog, a spec corpus), add a Dashboard / Index table at the top with stable anchor links into the body. Keep existing body content unchanged below — do **not** reorganize by topic / module, because the chronological + source-spec context is load-bearing.
- **Archive split at ship time.** Shipped / resolved entries are cut from the active doc into a sibling `*-archive.md` (do not annotate inline with Status blocks). Preserve cross-reference IDs with HTML anchors (`<a id="d-foo"></a>`).
